Broad in scope, embedded technologies help make consumer electronics better, allowing for more capabilities from the products we use in our everyday lives. Features and products such as extended memory for digital cameras, a home network capable of controlling a home's heating and cooling systems, or cell phones with voice recognition dialing are just a few examples of how embedded technologies are virtually limitless, adding to the value and efficiency of consumer electronics products across the board.
<br><br>
These technologies will continue to play a vital role in coming years. From debates on intellectual property issues to making our lives safer, these technologies can help offer solutions.
<br><br>
Embedded technologies will certainly be out in the open at the 2002 CES.

