<a name="entertainment"></a>
<font class="righttext">
<img src="/global_images/techwed.gif"><br>

Today's technology is making it possible for consumers to not only choose their content, but when and how they'll receive it. Consumers are avidly creating their content from MP3s of favorite hits or home movies with special effects. Digital technologies make content truly portable by allowing storage of astounding amounts of content in very small packages.
<br><br>
The quality of the experience continues to amaze. Surround-sound technology transforms the home audio experience into an experience like that of state-of-the-art movie theaters. And digital technologies continue to enhance the sound and picture quality for a truly "life-like" experience.
<br><br>
Broadband connections give us instant access to a wealth of information and entertainment options on the Internet. How soon will broadband move into the "living room" to provide more interactivity and content options?
<br><br>
International CES is the only show that brings all facets of entertainment and information together. Entertainment is foremost about content--whether it's the type of game you play, your radio format of choice, how you get your news or an e-mail message from your best friend. CES showcases the content development tools, such as digital cameras and editing software. You'll see a dazzling array of devices for displaying content such as DTVs, PDAs, wireless phones and home appliances. And finally, you'll find the companies that provide content delivery-the pipelines that bring the content to the consumer including satellite, narrowband, broadband and more. 
<br><br>
Explore CES to see what's available now…and enjoy a thrilling glimpse into the near future.
<br><br>

